{
  "text": "For sensitive values like database passwords, we use Pulumi Secrets. Secrets are encrypted at rest and in transit. You can set secrets using Pulumi Config set with the secret flag, or by using the Pulumi service which automatically encrypts secrets. In the code, we read secrets using config.requireSecret, which ensures the value exists and is treated as sensitive. Pulumi will never print secret values in logs or outputs. This is the secure way to handle passwords, ABI keys, and other sensitive config art.",
